CHANGELOG.md:86:- Added depth-2 sampler-scheduler end-to-end test coverage (frac-0114): `tests/test_sampler_scheduler.py` now includes `SamplerSchedulerEndToEndTests`, which drives `senseweave.sampler_scheduler` through one realistic scheduling lifecycle: `density_for_mode("evening_reflection")` resolves through `DEFAULT_SAMPLER_DENSITY_BY_MODE` to `0.65`, `count_sampler_events(0.65, 16, Random(42))` returns the documented `floor(0.65 * 16) + Bernoulli(0.65)` count under a deterministic RNG, `plan_sampler_phrase_indices(0.65, 16, Random(42))` returns sorted, unique, in-range phrase indices whose length matches that count, and a primitive diagnostic of the mode/density/count/indices round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_sampler_scheduler_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `senseweave.sampler_scheduler` already produced the required one-path floor + Bernoulli + sorted-sample output; startup identity anchors remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
