docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:198:## Process Issue: Default Launcher Should Use `run` Not `orchestrate`
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:205:exec sdp-cli orchestrate --start-phase development --end-phase development
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:208:`orchestrate` is a single-run command that exits when it finishes a phase. For an unattended 24/7 runner, this is the wrong primitive — it should be `run` (which loops until interrupted) or `run --force` (which also bypasses the breaker).
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:216:exec sdp-cli orchestrate --start-phase development --end-phase development
docs/sdp-cli-findings-report.md:222:And add to the sdp-cli docs: "For unattended systemd-managed runners, use `sdp-cli run`. Reserve `orchestrate` for interactive use where a human watches the output."
