./CHANGELOG.md:144:- Added depth-2 mix-verify end-to-end test coverage (frac-0089): `tests/test_mix_verify.py` now includes `MixVerifyEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/mix_verify.py` public surface through occupied-day mix profile construction, deterministic multi-voice synthetic rendering, profile and mastering validation, LUFS/peak/RMS measurement, clipping/silence checks, low-end and harshness reports, masking checks, render-loudness verification, and JSON-safe diagnostic serialization. `tests/test_test_mix_verify_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production mix verification behavior remains unchanged because it already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4568 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:318:- Added a stdlib-only narrative API smoke CLI (T-016@20260502T001347Za): `scripts/smoke_narrative.py` reads the base URL from `--base-url` or `NARRATIVE_BASE_URL` (defaulting to `http://cypherclaw:8765`), performs `GET /health` against `cypherclaw.narrative_api`, prints status code plus a 200-char body preview, and exits non-zero on any non-2xx response or connection failure. The optional `--token` flag is sent as the `X-Narrative-Auth` shared-secret header that the API enforces when `NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` is set, so the Deniable operator can validate the service from their Mac over Tailscale without a virtualenv. Documented in `README.md`; regression coverage in `tests/test_smoke_narrative_script.py` pins the success path, non-2xx exit, unreachable-host exit, header propagation, and body truncation.
./CHANGELOG.md:350:- Added a live Replicate smoke test for the generation backend (T-005): `tests/test_generation_live_replicate.py` exercises `ReplicateClient.generate(req)` against the real Replicate API with a fixed prompt and seed, and asserts a >100 KB WAV payload, `cost_usd` inside `[$0.01, $0.50]`, and `latency_ms < 60000`. The test is gated behind both the new `--run-live-replicate` pytest flag (registered in `tests/conftest.py` alongside the existing `--run-live-modal` seam) and a non-empty `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, so the default `pytest tests/` run skips it. Documented as ~$0.10 per opted-in run.
./CHANGELOG.md:352:- Added a local Ada generation backend stub: `senseweave.generation.client_local.LocalAdaClient` now satisfies the shared `GenerationClient` Protocol shape while raising `NotImplementedError("LocalAdaClient: GPU not yet installed; use Replicate or Modal")` until the local GPU path is installed. Added focused tests and an explicit mypy check for Protocol satisfaction.
./CHANGELOG.md:354:- Implemented `ModalClient` satisfying `GenerationClient` Protocol in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py`, enabling CypherClaw to use Modal serverless for generation (CCG-012). The client computes A10G runtime cost from metadata and gracefully degrades when the `modal` SDK is not installed. Also added protocol parity tests and gated live Modal tests behind `--run-live-modal`.
./CHANGELOG.md:389:- Implemented ST1-ST6 of the score-tree songwriting stack end to end: added `piece_commission.py`, `piece_brief.py`, `form_grammar.py`, `score_tree.py`, `recursive_composer.py`, `composition_gate.py`, `tracker_compiler.py`, and `piece_queue.py`; extended `repertoire_memory.py` to store structural score-tree summaries; and rewired `duet_composer.py` so tracker solo mode can commission a piece, build a complete score tree, gate it, compile it into tracker scenes, and precompose the next piece into a small persistent queue instead of treating the tracker as the composer.
